REMARK   3  AUTHORS STATE THAT: THE BOUNDARIES FOR STRETCHES OF MISSING         
REMARK   3  RESIDUES WERE DETERMINED USING A COMPOSITE OMIT MAP WITH A ONE-     
REMARK   3  SIGMA CUTOFF.                                                       
REMARK   3  ATOMS MODELED WITH ZERO OCCUPANCY COULD NOT BE PLACED WITH          
REMARK   3  CONFIDENCE AND WERE SELECTED FOR ZERO-OCCUPANCY FLAGGING AFTER      
REMARK   3  MANUAL INSPECTION OF THE 2FO-FC MAP AT A 0.5-SIGMA CUTOFF.          
REMARK   3  ALTHOUGH THE CORRELATION IS LOW, RESIDUES FLAGGED AS RSRZ OUTLIERS  
REMARK   3  HAVE REASONABLE CONCORDANCE WITH THE 2FO-FC MAP, ARE NOT ROTAMER    
REMARK   3  OUTLIERS, AND ARE DEVOID OF CLASHES WITH NEIGHBORING ATOMS.         
REMARK   3  POSITIVE DENSITY PEAKS GREATER THAN 4-SIGMA WERE IDENTIFIED THAT    
REMARK   3  COULD NOT BE EXPLAINED BY MODELING WATER OR COMPONENTS FROM THE     
REMARK   3  CRYSTALLIZATION BUFFER AND WERE NOT MODELED.                        
